Hotel of Longboat Key \n\nJohn and Mable Ringling dreamed of more than just an art museum\u2014they envisioned Sarasota as a world-class destination. In the 1920s, John set out to build a lavish Ritz-Carlton Hotel on Longboat Key. To make it happen, he donated land, constructed a causeway, and invested $400K of his own funds.\n \nThough the hotel was never completed\u2014derailed by a massive hurricane and market crashes\u2014it left a lasting imprint on Sarasota\u2019s history.\n\nToday, thanks to the Ringlings\u2019 vision, Sarasota continues to thrive as a cultural destination!\n\n\u26abGhost Hotel of Longboat Key. n.d.
